<subSubSection id="038BB7F1FFBDFFDC74D1FBFEF81FFA00" pageId="17" pageNumber="38" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="4B2EE47AFFBDFFDC74D1FBFEF8EEFB33" blockId="17.[151,427,1146,1172]" box="[151,427,1146,1172]" pageId="17" pageNumber="38">
<heading id="10665316FFBDFFDC74D1FBFEF8EEFB33" bold="true" box="[151,427,1146,1172]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="17" pageNumber="38" reason="1">
<taxonomicName id="8C919FF9FFBDFFDC74D1FBFEF8EEFB33" authority="Latreille, 1804" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1804" box="[151,427,1146,1172]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="79E53868FFBDFFDC74D1FBFEF8EEFB33" bold="true" box="[151,427,1146,1172]" pageId="17" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis id="79E53868FFBDFFDC74D1FBFEF9AAFB33" bold="true" box="[151,239,1146,1172]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="38">Ponera</emphasis>
Latreille, 
<number id="FD59F65DFFBDFFDC7536FBFEF8EEFB33" box="[368,427,1146,1172]" pageId="17" pageNumber="38" value="1804.0">1804</number>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4B2EE47AFFBDFFDC74D1FB41F81FFA00" blockId="17.[151,1436,1221,1647]" pageId="17" pageNumber="38">Males winged. Antennal scrobe absent. Mandible reduced in size. Basal cavity of mandible extending to its front face, visible in full-face view. Notauli absent. Mesepimeron without epimeral lobe. Each dorsolateral corner of petiole in anterior view lacking distinct projection. Dorsal margin petiole, in anterior view, without narrowly rounded or pointed apex. Apical margin of abdominal tergum VIII strongly projecting into sharp spine. Jugal lobe of hind wing absent. Middle and hind tibiae with single spur. Claws simple, never multidentate or pectinate.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="038BB7F1FFBDFFDC7480FA31FB34F9C8" pageId="17" pageNumber="38" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4B2EE47AFFBDFFDC7480FA31FB34F9C8" blockId="17.[151,1436,1221,1647]" pageId="17" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis id="79E53868FFBDFFDC7480FA31F87CFA68" bold="true" box="[198,313,1461,1487]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="38">Remarks.</emphasis>
Only a single species is known from this region at present. Although the species is not rare, no males were found in material examined for this study. The above diagnosis is based on 
<bibRefCitation id="2F00998BFFBDFFDC70E5FA59FC0CFA50" author="Taylor" box="[1187,1353,1501,1527]" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" refString="Taylor, R. W. (1967) A monographic revision of the ant genus Ponera Latreille (Hymenoptera: Formicidae). Pacific Insects Monograph, 13: 1 - 112." type="journal article" year="1967">
Taylor (
<number id="FD59F65DFFBDFFDC7146FA59FC05FA50" box="[1280,1344,1501,1527]" pageId="17" pageNumber="38" value="1967.0">1967</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Males are similar to those in 
<taxonomicName id="8C919FF9FFBDFFDC75E4F981FB70F9B9" box="[418,565,1541,1566]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Hypoponera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="79E53868FFBDFFDC75E4F981FB70F9B9" box="[418,565,1541,1566]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="38">Hypoponera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished from the latter in having a distinct spine on the apical portion of abdominal tergum VIII. This character was given in 
<figureCitation id="D3AAF8FFFFBDFFDC779FF9A9FD0EF9E0" box="[985,1099,1581,1607]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="18.[151,255,1771,1795]" captionTargetBox="[199,1381,370,1744]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[194,1393,370,1757]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 10. Male of Platythyrea Mad 02 (CASENT 0442287). (a) head to abdomen in lateral view; (b) head in full-face view; (c) head to abdomen in dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274013/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="38">
Figure 
<number id="FD59F65DFFBDFFDC7068F9A9FD0EF9E0" box="[1070,1099,1581,1607]" pageId="17" pageNumber="38" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
of Taylorâ€™s revision (
<number id="FD59F65DFFBDFFDC7109F9A9FCCBF9E0" box="[1359,1422,1581,1607]" pageId="17" pageNumber="38" value="1967.0">1967</number>
), although erroneously explained as 
<collectionCode id="2D807CBFFFBDFFDC7669F9D1FB28F9C8" box="[559,621,1621,1647]" pageId="17" pageNumber="38">AVII</collectionCode>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
